"     <br>",
"      * The decision of which studies to send depends upon the individual patient's clinical findings and on availability at specific hospital laboratories. When the diagnosis is not established by studies of bronchoalveolar lavage fluid or non-invasive testing, histopathology of lung tissue is often helpful. For detailed discussions regarding the diagnosis of specific causes of pneumonia, see individual topic reviews.",
"      <br>",
"       &bull; The detection of Candida species from respiratory specimens should generally be interpreted as reflecting colonization of the oropharynx since Candida pneumonia is extremely rare.",
